flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Hourly ingestion of actual production events and schedule reconciliation showing deviation beyond configurable thresholds (e.g., yield loss, throughput gap, or changeover delay).]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Ingest hourly schedule, work orders, capacity and event streams into DI foundation.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: RCA Service - Detect deviation and perform root-cause analysis against recent events and constraints.]
  N2 --> N3{Agent: Process (Process Builder) + Agent Team + Remote Functions - Agentic decisioning invokes deterministic scheduler and constraint checks, producing corrective plan.}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions + Transaction - Apply the revised schedule and changeover plan to ERP and operations; trigger downstream actions.]
  N4 --> N5[PB: UI Screen - Surface actionable recommendations and exception details to planners and line leaders for review.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification + CWB Lifecycle - Notify stakeholders of applied changes and monitor recovery performance until back on-track.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Faster recovery from disruptions, reduced unplanned changeover time and line idle, improved on-time-in-full (OTIF), lower emergency inventory and WIP, and measurable COGS reduction through higher throughput and less rework.]
  N3 -->|Insufficient or stale MES / IIoT data...| B1[Agent Team requests missing data, falls back to conservative safe schedule (minimize risk), and notifies planners via CWB.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Safe fallback schedule enacted; manual intervention queued and data quality work item created.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Optimizer recommends schedule that vi...| B2[Route recommendation to CWB Lifecycle for mandatory human approval and provide constraint-violation rationale.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Human review either approves adjusted plan with mitigation actions or rejects and triggers alternative plan generation.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Multi-line or multi-plant conflict di...| B3[Spawn multi-agent negotiation (Agent Team Multi-Agent Pipeline) to reallocate capacity, adjust PO timing, and coordinate changeovers across plants.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Negotiated, constraint-compliant multi-plant plan produced and committed; supply/procurement notified for any PO changes.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]